I really am not a fan of this way of selecting "foo" as the default to compare too. Would prefer something like:
Set<String> concreteVars = computeConcreteVars();
Set<String> symbolicVars = computeSymbolicVars();
if ((! (concreteVars.isEmpty() && symbolicVars.isEmpty())) && hasSimplification()) {
   error("Can't have concrete/symbolic without simplification");
}
if (concreteVars.intersects(symbolicVars)) {
   error("Can't have the same variable both concrete/symbolic: " concreteVars.intersection(symbolicVars));
}

The logic you have here is pretty hard to read.

